Procedure.description:
Procedure Purpose: SAT REPSEQ Update
Procedure Version: 2 Responsibility: Claudia Tranquilli Last Modified Date: 25.07.2022
Change History: Version 2: (CT - 25.07.2022) - Removed argument for PAF ID and removed FDC_PART from arguments PART_IDs, as not compatible with commanding.
Version 1: (CT - 14.12.2021) - Copied from FOM procedure N_SAT_I520 version 4 (delivered in FOM5) - Procedure Description field updated according to EUMETSAT template; - Procedure History field erased and restarted from Version 1; - Procedure updated to acquire PAF and call FOP procedure N_SYS_0701 for PF REPSEQ update.
Procedure Objectives:
- This procedure uploads a new Repeat Sequence to both FCI and PF.
Procedure Overview:
This procedure acquires PAF file for REPSEQ update at PF and FCI level accordingly.
Procedure Pre-conditions: None
Procedure Constraints: None
Spacecraft Configuration: Procedure is executed as part of FCI SCAN Setup or Scan Pattern update. Therefore, the SC configuration is FPM/NOM with FCI in WAIT or OBSERVATION mode.
Ground Segment Configuration: None
Remarks: None
